## Results
results on the eﬀectiveness of EFT for depression, and
insight into mechanisms of change.
Major Depressive Disorder (MDD) is the world’s leading cause of medical disability (World
Health Organization, 2017), and is associated with costs exceeding $219 billion in the United States
each year (Greenberg, Fournier, Sisitsky, Pike, & Kessler, 2015). There is a strong, bidirectional
association between MDD and relationship distress for both men and women (Davila, Karney,
Andrea K. Wittenborn, PhD, Human Development and Family Studies, Michigan State University, East Lans-
ing, MI and Psychiatry and Behavioral Medicine, Michigan State University, Grand Rapids, MI; Ting Liu, PhD,
Philadelphia Center for Emotionally Focused Therapy, Philadelphia, PA; Ty A. Ridenour, PhD, RTI International,
Research Triangle Park, NC; E. Megan Lachmar, MS, Human Development and Family Studies, Michigan State
University, East Lansing, MI; Erica A. Mitchell, MS, Human Development and Family Studies, Michigan State
University, East Lansing, MI; Ryan B. Seedall, PhD, Human Development and Family Studies, Utah State Univer-
sity, Logan, UT.
